{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Multiple maps using subplots\n",
    "============================="
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Populating the interactive namespace from numpy and matplotlib\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import ee\n",
    "import cartoee as cee\n",
    "import cartopy.crs as ccrs\n",
    "\n",
    "%pylab inline"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ee.Initialize()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Seasonal NDVI example\n",
    "\n",
    "In this example we will compute the seasonal average NDVI values for the globe and plot the four seasons on the same figure."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# function to add NDVI band to imagery\n",
    "def calc_ndvi(img):\n",
    "    ndvi = img.normalizedDifference(['Nadir_Reflectance_Band2','Nadir_Reflectance_Band1'])\n",
    "    return img.addBands(ndvi.rename('ndvi'))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# MODIS Nadir BRDF-Adjusted Reflectance with NDVI band\n",
    "modis = ee.ImageCollection('MODIS/006/MCD43A4')\\\n",
    "        .filterDate('2010-01-01','2016-01-01')\\\n",
    "        .map(calc_ndvi)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# set parameters for plotting\n",
    "ndviVis = {'min':-0.5,'max':0.85,'bands':'ndvi','palette':'d73027,fc8d59,fee08b,ffffbf,d9ef8b,91cf60,1a9850'}\n",
    "bbox = [-180,-60,180,90]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# get land mass feature collection\n",
    "land = ee.FeatureCollection('USDOS/LSIB_SIMPLE/2017')\n",
    "\n",
    "# calculate seasonal averages and clip to land features\n",
    "djf = modis.filter(ee.Filter.calendarRange(12,3,'month')).mean().clip(land)\n",
    "mam = modis.filter(ee.Filter.calendarRange(3,6,'month')).mean().clip(land)\n",
    "jja = modis.filter(ee.Filter.calendarRange(6,9,'month')).mean().clip(land)\n",
    "son = modis.filter(ee.Filter.calendarRange(9,12,'month')).mean().clip(land)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x504 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# set up a blank map with multiple subplots\n",
    "fig,ax = plt.subplots(ncols=2,nrows=2,figsize=(10,7),subplot_kw={'projection': ccrs.Orthographic(-80,35)})\n",
    "\n",
    "# format images and subplot titles with same dimensions as subplots\n",
    "imgs = np.array([[djf,mam],[jja,son]])\n",
    "titles = np.array([['DJF','MAM'],['JJA','SON']])\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(len(imgs)):\n",
    "    for j in range(len(imgs[i])):\n",
    "        ax[i,j] = cee.addLayer(imgs[i,j],ax=ax[i,j],\n",
    "                               region=bbox,dims=500,\n",
    "                               visParams=ndviVis\n",
    "                              )\n",
    "        ax[i,j].coastlines()\n",
    "        ax[i,j].gridlines(linestyle='--')\n",
    "        ax[i,j].set_title(titles[i,j])\n",
    "        \n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Map inset example\n",
    "\n",
    "In this example we are going to take a region image from EE, plot the entire region, and plot a smaller country within the region as a subset. This specific example will create a map for West Africa showing a Landsat mosaic and create an inset map of Senegal using the same Landsat mosaic."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# get a country FeatureCollection\n",
    "countries = ee.FeatureCollection('USDOS/LSIB_SIMPLE/2017')\n",
    "# filter the countries for a specific county\n",
    "country = 'Senegal'\n",
    "senegal = ee.Feature(countries.filter(ee.Filter.eq('country_na',country)).first())\n",
    "# create an ee.Image from a FeatureCollection\n",
    "adminImg = ee.Image().paint(countries,color='#000000',width=4)\n",
    "\n",
    "# get a Landsat mosaic for West Africa\n",
    "waLandsat = ee.Image('projects/servir-wa/regional_west_africa/Landsat_SR/Landsat_SR_prewet_2012_2014')\n",
    "# specify the visualization parameters\n",
    "lsVis = {'min':50,'max':5500,'gamma':1.5,'bands':'swir2,nir,green'}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1080x504 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# import some styling functions\n",
    "from cartopy.mpl.gridliner import LATITUDE_FORMATTER, LONGITUDE_FORMATTER\n",
    "\n",
    "# setup blank figure\n",
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(15,7))\n",
    "\n",
    "# region for the main map\n",
    "mainBox = [-17.5,3.5,24.5,25.5]\n",
    "\n",
    "# set blank map for the main plot and add layers\n",
    "ax_main = fig.add_subplot(1, 1, 1,projection=ccrs.PlateCarree())\n",
    "ax_main = cee.addLayer(waLandsat,visParams=lsVis,region=mainBox,dims=2500,ax=ax_main)\n",
    "ax_main = cee.addLayer(adminImg,region=mainBox,dims=1500,ax=ax_main)\n",
    "\n",
    "# main map styling\n",
    "xmain = np.linspace(-17.5,24.5,5)\n",
    "ymain = np.linspace(3.5,25.5,3)\n",
    "ax_main.gridlines(xlocs=xmain, ylocs=ymain,linestyle=':')\n",
    "# set custom formatting for the tick labels\n",
    "ax_main.xaxis.set_major_formatter(LONGITUDE_FORMATTER)\n",
    "ax_main.yaxis.set_major_formatter(LATITUDE_FORMATTER)\n",
    "# set tick labels\n",
    "ax_main.set_xticks(xmain, crs=ccrs.PlateCarree())\n",
    "ax_main.set_yticks(ymain, crs=ccrs.PlateCarree())\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# region for the map inset\n",
    "insetBox = [-17.5,12,-11,17]\n",
    "\n",
    "# setup inset map and add layers\n",
    "ax_inset = fig.add_axes([0.45, 0.5, 0.6, 0.5],projection=ccrs.PlateCarree())\n",
    "ax_inset = cee.addLayer(waLandsat.clip(senegal),visParams=lsVis,region=insetBox,dims=2500,ax=ax_inset)\n",
    "ax_inset = cee.addLayer(adminImg,region=insetBox,ax=ax_inset)\n",
    "\n",
    "# inset map styling\n",
    "xinset = np.linspace(-17.5,-11,5)\n",
    "yinset = np.linspace(12,17,3)\n",
    "ax_inset.gridlines(xlocs=xinset, ylocs=yinset,linestyle=':')\n",
    "# set custom formatting for the tick labels\n",
    "ax_inset.xaxis.set_major_formatter(LONGITUDE_FORMATTER)\n",
    "ax_inset.yaxis.set_major_formatter(LATITUDE_FORMATTER)\n",
    "ax_inset.xaxis.tick_top()\n",
    "ax_inset.yaxis.tick_right()\n",
    "# set inset tick labels\n",
    "ax_inset.set_xticks(xinset, crs=ccrs.PlateCarree())\n",
    "ax_inset.set_yticks(yinset, crs=ccrs.PlateCarree())\n",
    "\n",
    "# add some text to the inset as a pseudo-title\n",
    "ax_inset.text(-12.63,16.5,country,fontsize=16,bbox=dict(facecolor='white', alpha=0.5,edgecolor='k'))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  }
 ],
